{"source_hash": "fcb5f3d015cf6ae4", "candidate": {"id": "cand-023", "name": "Daniel Okonkwo", "raw_cv": "DANIEL OKONKWO\ndaniel.okonkwo@email.com | Manchester, UK (willing to relocate)\n\nSENIOR SOFTWARE ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nSenior software engineer with 8 years of experience in enterprise Java backends and cloud-native microservices. Specialist in Spring Boot, AWS, and high-availability system design. Strong background in financial services and insurance technology.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSenior Software Engineer \u2014 Aviva Digital, Manchester (2020\u2013present)\n- Lead engineer on the claims processing platform serving 2M+ policy holders\n- Designed and delivered microservices migration from a 12-year-old J2EE monolith to Spring Boot + AWS\n- Introduced contract testing (Pact) across 18 microservices, eliminating integration regressions\n- Line-managed 2 engineers; ran weekly architecture guild sessions\n\nSoftware Engineer \u2014 Lloyds Banking Group, Halifax (2017\u20132020)\n- Backend engineer on the mortgage origination system (Java, IBM MQ, Oracle DB)\n- Contributed to Open Banking API implementation (PSD2 compliance)\n- Led a cross-functional team delivering GDPR data deletion features under tight regulatory timeline\n\nJunior Software Engineer \u2014 Capgemini, Manchester (2016\u20132017)\n- Consultant on Java EE projects for public sector clients\n\nSKILLS\nJava 17, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, AWS (ECS, SQS, SNS, RDS), PostgreSQL, Oracle, Kafka, Docker, Kubernetes, Pact, JUnit 5, Gradle\n\nEDUCATION\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 University of Manchester (2013\u20132016)\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nBritish citizen (Nigerian heritage)", "raw_linkedin": "Senior software engineer with eight years in enterprise Java, mostly in financial services. I've spent my career modernising legacy systems \u2014 moving things off J2EE monoliths and onto cloud-native microservices that are actually testable and deployable. At Aviva I've been leading a migration that's been running for three years and is finally in the home straight. I care a lot about engineering craft: contract testing, proper observability, sensible API design. Ready for a new challenge after a long tenure \u2014 ideally somewhere with more greenfield work and a faster release cadence. Open to London relocation.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: Daniel, thanks for making the trip down. Tell me about the claims platform migration.\n\nDaniel: It's been the defining project of my time at Aviva. We inherited a J2EE monolith that had been in production since 2012 \u2014 no unit tests, deployments were monthly at best, and the team was afraid to touch large parts of it. The business case for migration was a big regulatory change that the old system genuinely couldn't accommodate. We spent six months designing the target architecture \u2014 event-driven microservices on AWS ECS, Kafka as the backbone \u2014 and then three years executing it in parallel with keeping the old system running. We're now at about 80% migrated.\n\nInterviewer: What's been the hardest part of that migration?\n\nDaniel: Data. The legacy system had a single Oracle database with 300+ tables, lots of implicit coupling. Untangling the data ownership so each service could have its own store took longer than the code migration. We used the Strangler Fig pattern which helped, but there were still some very tricky moments.\n\nInterviewer: This role is London-based, 4 days in the office. You mentioned you're willing to relocate?\n\nDaniel: Yes, I'm ready for that change. Manchester's been great but I want to be in a more concentrated tech scene. I've already been viewing flats.\n\nInterviewer: Salary expectations?\n\nDaniel: I'm on \u00a389,000 at Aviva. I'd be looking for \u00a395\u2013105,000 for the relocation and step up.", "years_experience": 8.0, "skills": ["Java 17", "Spring Boot", "Spring Cloud", "AWS (ECS, SQS, SNS, RDS)", "PostgreSQL", "Oracle", "Kafka", "Docker", "Kubernetes", "Pact", "JUnit 5", "Gradle", "microservices", "cloud-native", "system design", "contract testing", "observability", "API design"], "industries": ["financial services", "insurance technology", "banking"], "seniority_level": "senior", "management_experience": true, "education_level": "bachelor", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.85, "culture_fit_score": 0.8, "constraints": [{"id": "939d9e62", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary at Aviva is \u00a389,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 89000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "bb53204e", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation for new role: \u00a395,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 95000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "93fbd9bb", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Maximum salary expectation for new role: \u00a3105,000 (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 105000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.96, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "a555d063", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Willing and ready to relocate from Manchester (stated in interview and CV)", "canonical_key": "relocation_required", "value": true, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": null}, {"id": "4a8150e0", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Prefers London relocation; actively viewing flats (stated in interview)", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94, "currency": null}, {"id": "6a742be8", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_arrangement", "description": "Accepting of 4 days in office per week (stated in interview context)", "canonical_key": "office_days_per_week", "value": 4.0, "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.92, "currency": null}, {"id": "8caad057", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_environment", "description": "Preference for greenfield/new work rather than legacy maintenance (stated in LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "greenfield work", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "27e74ec2", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "work_environment", "description": "Prefers faster release cadence; ready for new challenge after long tenure at Aviva (stated in LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "faster release cadence", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "96f2a519", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "culture", "description": "Values engineering craft: contract testing, observability, API design (stated in LinkedIn)", "canonical_key": null, "value": "engineering craft focus", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.88, "currency": null}]}, "embedding": [0.02117919921875, 0.04205322265625, 0.07958984375, -0.0164031982421875, -0.0017871856689453125, 0.0008821487426757812, 0.010986328125, 0.0164337158203125, 0.0274658203125, -0.007476806640625, -0.005413055419921875, -0.06640625, -0.01517486572265625, 0.0390625, 0.050994873046875, 0.0418701171875, -0.01099395751953125, 0.0022182464599609375, -0.050048828125, -7.587671279907227e-05, 0.0086517333984375, 0.006458282470703125, -0.0297698974609375, 0.047088623046875, -0.000881195068359375, -0.058319091796875, -0.05926513671875, 0.00272369384765625, -0.0023899078369140625, -0.07196044921875, 0.036407470703125, -0.030975341796875, -0.0086669921875, 0.06707763671875, 0.035247802734375, -0.02935791015625, 0.0039825439453125, 0.0234222412109375, 0.0214080810546875, -0.03961181640625, -0.0176849365234375, -